<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-06-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="52" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6847/1–2.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Ambassador of
                                    Austria-Hungary</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Austro-Hungarian Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-06-12"><hi rend="italic">June 12,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1156.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge,
                            with thanks, the receipt of your valued communication, No. 257, of the
                            8th instant, and to append hereto a corrected list<note n="a" xml:id="d52fna">Not printed.</note> of the districts and incumbents
                            of imperial and royal consular offices in the United States and its
                            insular possessions.</p>
                        <p>I have to add, at the same time, that my Government has received no
                            complaint of the character described in my note, No. 1087, of the 23d
                            [30th] ultimo from the consular officers in Porto Rico, Hawaii, and the
                            Philippine Islands.</p>
                        <p>Accept, excellency, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hengelmuller.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>